body:
I'm trying to render a component with react-test-renderer that is trying to get the `parentElement.offsetWidth` inside the `useEffect` hook.

The ref is attached to a SVG element and is trying to get the width of the parent node, that's why I need to use the reference to get the element after render.

The code is something like this:

```javascript
...
const svgRef = useRef();
const [{ width, height, isSizeSet }, setSize] = useState({
    width: 0,
    height: 0,
    isSizeSet: false,
  });

const handleResize = () => {
    const offsetWidth = svgRef.current.parentElement.offsetWidth;
    if ((svgWidth || svgHeight) && !isSizeSet) {
      setSize({
        ...getSize(svgWidth, svgHeight, margin, aspectRatio),
        isSizeSet: true,
      });
    } else if (offsetWidth !== svgWidth - (margin.left + margin.right)) {
      setSize({
        ...getSize(offsetWidth, undefined, margin, aspectRatio),
        isSizeSet: true,
      });
    }
  };

  useEffect(() => {
    handleResize();
    window.addEventListener('resize', handleResize);

    return () => {
      window.removeEventListener('resize', handleResize);
    };
  }, []);

return (
  <SVG ref={svgRef} ... />
)
...
```

When I run the test I'm getting an error message saying `TypeError: Cannot read property 'parentElement' of null` and the only thing I'm trying to do is to render the component.

This test was working prior adding the `useEffect` hook to it.

```javascript
test('Should render correctly', () => {
  const tree = create(<Component data={data} />).toJSON();
  expect(tree).toMatchSnapshot();
});
```

I'm currently using `react@16.7.0-alpha.2`, `react-dom@16.7.0-alpha.2`, and `react-test-renderer@16.7.0-alpha.2` using `jest@23.6.0` on macOS and I wonder if there is a way to mock this object or there anything else that I have to do and don't know?

I couldn't find info about how to deal with references in the tests using useEffect.
